imdb.plot outline: In Conversation with Alex Malley is an Australian television interview show on the Nine Network. Alex Malley, the chief executive of CPA Australia, conducts one-on-one interviews with leaders from the world of politics, business, entertainment or the community. The show is a co production between CPA Australia and the Nine Network Australia. The eight part series first screened on Sunday 7 February 2016 at 10.00am as "The Conversation with Alex Malley". The second series is currently airing Sundays at 10.00am on the Nine Network. Following on from the tremendous success of three seasons of The Bottom Line, In Conversation with Alex Malley reveals the moving life stories of influential leaders. The inspiring, thought-provoking guests discuss their big lives and how they've made a real difference, through conversations with Alex. Eight leaders will feature in season two including: the king of waltz Andre Rieu; AFL legend and Cure for MND Foundation Patron Neale Daniher; journalist and TV presenter Peter Overton; Australia's most famous activist Germaine Greer; surfing sensation and seven time world champion Layne Beachley; Australia's most successful theatre producer John Frost; Australian High Commissioner to the UK Alexander Downer and burns specialist, Professor Fiona Wood.
